---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  path="/beyond/"
  title="Beyond research"
  description="Teaching, service, and the things that have nothing to do with the job."
>
  <h1>Beyond research</h1>

  <div class="prose">
    <p>
      The page for everything that does not belong on a CV but is still true.
      Teaching and outreach, the committee you sit on, the sport you have not
      quit, the thing you built for no reason. It is usually the page people
      remember, and it costs nothing to keep honest and short.
    </p>

    <h2>Teaching and service</h2>
    <p>
      Mentoring, outreach, reviewing, the seminar you organise. Name the
      programme and link it — this is work, and it is the work most likely to
      go unrecorded anywhere else.
    </p>

    <figure class="figure--media figure--pair">
      <div class="figure__grid">
        <img
          src="/img/figure-wide.jpg"
          alt="Placeholder figure — replace or delete"
          width="1000"
          height="750"
          loading="lazy"
          decoding="async"
        />
        <img
          src="/img/figure-wide-b.jpg"
          alt="Placeholder figure — replace or delete"
          width="1000"
          height="750"
          loading="lazy"
          decoding="async"
        />
      </div>
      <figcaption>
        Where and when, in that order. A caption that reads “IMG_4127” is a
        caption you have not written yet.
      </figcaption>
    </figure>

    <h2>Everything else</h2>
    <p>
      Keep a couple of short sections rather than one long one. The mount also
      takes a <code>&lt;video&gt;</code> or an <code>&lt;iframe&gt;</code> —
      give either a <code>width</code> and <code>height</code> so the page does
      not jump while it loads, and set <code>preload="none"</code> on video so
      a visitor who never presses play never pays for it.
    </p>

    <h2>A section you should delete</h2>
    <p>
      Along with this whole page, if it is not for you. Remove
      <code>src/pages/beyond.astro</code> and drop the matching entry from
      <code>nav</code> in <code>src/data/site.js</code>; nothing else refers to
      it.
    </p>
  </div>
</Base>
